ZCZC EE25
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 082300 UTC
ON SUNDAY EVENING LOW PRESSURE AROUND 968 IS EXP TO BE
CENTRED NEAR NERN SCOTLAND WITH ANOTHER LOW CENTRE 980
OVER FASTNET. THESE LOW PRESSURE SYSTEMS TRANSFERRING
EWARDS THROUGH THE PERIOD TO FORM A LARGE LOW 985 TO
THE S OF FINLAND BY MIDNIGHT WEDNESDAY. ALSO BY
WEDNESDAY A SHALLOWER LOW PRESSURE 1000 IS EXP TO
DEVELOP OVER FAIR ISLE OR FAEROES PERHAPS WITH A FURTHER
SHALLOW LOW 1010 NEAR HEBRIDES. HIGH 1050 IS EXP TO
DEVELOP OVER GREENLAND THROUGH THE PERIOD WITH RIDGE
EXTENDING SWARDS OVER THE N ATLANTIC AND ANOTHER RIDGE
FORMING OVER IBERIA. STRG WINDS ARE EXP TO AFFECT MUCH OF
NITON AT THE START OF THE PERIOD WITH GALE OR SEV GALE
FORCE WINDS LIKELY TO DEVELOP OVER MOST SEA AREAS EXCEPT
PERHAPS THE SW OF FITZROY ON MONDAY AND TUESDAY. WINDS
THEN TENDING TO EASE INTO WEDNESDAY
